{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80811", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80811/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80811/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80811/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/80811", "id": 782008234, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU3ODIwMDgyMzQ=", "number": 80811, "title": "Type inference issue when trait objects are used in combinations with closures", "user": {"login": "StyMaar", "id": 5692308, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2OTIzMDg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5692308?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar", "html_url": "https://github.com/StyMaar", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/StyMaar/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2021-01-08T10:15:56Z", "updated_at": "2021-01-08T14:46:52Z", "closed_at": "2021-01-08T13:45:58Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following snippet fails\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n\r\ntrait MyTrait {}\r\n\r\nstruct Foo{}\r\n\r\nimpl MyTrait for Foo {}\r\n\r\nfn foo() -> Result<Foo,()> {\r\n    Ok(Foo {})\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn bar()-> Result<Box<dyn MyTrait>, ()> {\r\n    foo().map(|foo| Box::new(foo))\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWith the following error : \r\n\r\n```\r\n12 | fn bar()-> Result<Box<dyn MyTrait>, ()> {\r\n   |            ---------------------------- expected `std::result::Result<Box<(dyn MyTrait + 'static)>, ()>` because of return type\r\n13 |     foo().map(|foo| Box::new(foo))\r\n   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ expected trait object `dyn MyTrait`, found struct `Foo`\r\n   |\r\n   = note: expected enum `std::result::Result<Box<(dyn MyTrait + 'static)>, _>`\r\n              found enum `std::result::Result<Box<Foo>, _>`\r\n```\r\nThe compiler is smart enough to infer the type after adding a simple `as _`, but it shouldn't be necessary.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntrait MyTrait {}\r\n\r\nstruct Foo{}\r\n\r\nimpl MyTrait for Foo {}\r\n\r\nfn foo() -> Result<Foo,()> {\r\n    Ok(Foo {})\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn bar()-> Result<Box<dyn MyTrait>, ()> {\r\n    foo().map(|foo| Box::new(foo) as _ )\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\nThis bug occurs in rust 1.49 stable and the current nightly as well (1.51.0-nightly (2021-01-07 c8915eebeaaef9f7cc1c))\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "jonas-schievink", "id": 1786438, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODY0Mzg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1786438?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonas-schievink", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "su